Description: Mentat is a blockchain-powered marketplace where apps can source intelligence from an on-demand, distributed workforce of human agents.
Full Description: Mentat is a blockchain-powered marketplace where applications can source intelligence from an on-demand, distributed workforce of human agents. The platform’s query-response smart contracts enable human intelligence tasks to plug in to computer processes asynchronously, eliminating the time and cost inefficiencies typically associated with human workers.  Mentat’s pricing model ensures that human agents are always available to meet the next request. The platform’s distributed ledger tracks agents’ unique skills, allowing applications to query only the most qualified agents, and a system of peer review maintains quality while moving more work towards the most successful agents. Crypto-economic stakes for all parties ensure fast, high-quality work and fair rates. Mentat enables anyone, from anywhere in the world, to offer their skills and knowledge in exchange for instant payment. By allowing applications to delegate only value-adding human intelligence tasks, the value of agents’ time is increased, while also improving the business efficiency of participating applications. Mentat combines a machine-focused process with human-focused pricing, allowing fair earnings and business efficiency to coexist.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US

Full Description: There is a lack of access to a verifiable historical record of affordable housing units and accountability from landlords to follow the law.  It is unacceptable that in 2020 the rent history was only available via a paper form. It is unacceptable that HPD does not have access to detailed data of affordable leases. It could be impossible to illegally deregulate a unit if the data was public. This information asymmetry largely contributes to tenant harassment. Tenants must go through complex administrative processes to get an answer.  Therefore tenants feel pressured to leave their apartments due to ongoing harassment and because they are unaware of their rights and how to fight back.  There are old and new challenges because of Covid that have made on the ground organizing difficult for local organizers and we offer some additional digital resources for better communication with tenants.  If not put on check, Landlord will continue to sidestep the housing laws and continue to raise rents and contribute to the gentrification and defunding of poor and vulnerable communities.   LOTB is designed to be the tool of systemic change on how the community deals with the lack of information about affordable housing. As of November 2020, LOTB suspended its activities

Description: B2B SaaS platform helping mobile teams communicate through instant message, collaborative task mapping, and delivery procurement modules.
Full Description: Cockpit Mobile creates a set of general tools to improve communication and execution amongst any team not sitting at a desk. Mobile teams frequently rely on phone calls and emails to communicate everything: Schedules, updates, documentation, pictures...the list goes on. Phone calls are siloed, only reaching those on the call. Emails are not made for instant communication and are messy when chains become long.  Cockpit Mobile's "Field General" creates instant messaging channels for each project. This help teams communicate in an organized fashion and also automatically documents correspondence into a master job file. A critical aspect of Field General is the ability to add subcontractors and clients to these instant messaging channels - traditional instant messaging such as Slack silo companies and make this difficult. Field General has 2 main use cases: venue/event management and delivery procurement.  Venue/event management consists of uploading a floorplan or layout and adding team members to that event. Management & staff can drag & drop virtual task lists across this map, pinning them to certain areas.  In real-time, the team is updated and can see what needs to be done, exactly where it needs to be done. They simply check off the item & can post proof of completion, helping their management and fellow team members understand progress and more efficiently execute. This has application in big box retail, construction, concerts, festivals, theme parks, campuses, and more. Our delivery module help bring the Uber feel to any home service or delivery (cable installation, mattress delivery, etc.). 4 hour windows are turned into real-time ETA notifications and a GPS view of the technician en route to your residence. The ability to instant message directly with the technician and drop a pin helps increase satisfaction for both parties. Additional modules such as virtual punchcards, equipment tracking, scheduling & dispatching help fill more specific needs of our partner companies.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Founders: Brandon Humboldt, Christopher Betagole, Clay Burdelik, Justin Beck

During an adjustment, some patients may hear a popping noise, similar to they would hear if they cracked their fingers. The discharge of nitrogen gas from a joint capsule causes the popping sound. Description: Heavy equipment telematics company made by equipment owners for equipment owners
Full Description: Clear Telematics was founded by materials handling equipment distributors who sought to harness the power of GPS telematics technology to better manage their extensive fleet of over 1,500 industrial machines. Their journey began with the challenges they faced in the North Dakota oil fields, where misplacing a unit or not tracking its runtime could result in several additional hours of travel. Their quest for a suitable telematics solution led them to try five different companies, but none met their expectations in terms of affordability and compatibility with their diverse fleet. Dissatisfied with the available options, they took matters into their own hands and crafted the telematics system they had envisioned. This system, Clear Telematics, is a GPS telematics device paired with fleet monitoring software, tailored to meet the practical needs of equipment owners without breaking the bank. What sets Clear Telematics apart is its affordability compared to other IoT fleet management solutions and its user-friendly design. Users can monitor vehicles, equipment, and machinery from various manufacturers all on a single dashboard. This includes heavy machinery, construction equipment, and commercial vans. Additionally, Clear Telematics offers an open API, allowing businesses to integrate their telematics data with their existing management software. The system is designed to be straightforward and durable, avoiding unnecessary features that could complicate the user experience and increase costs. At its core, Clear Telematics aims to provide essential data at a price point that ensures a tangible return on investment for its users.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Minneapolis-Saint Paul Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
